      "span_text": "At least one family member per sample, for both cases and controls, agreed to be interviewed for the purpose of a psychological autopsy, which generated an Axis I and Axis II diagnosis.  Depressed-suicide cases (N=25) were selected according to the following criteria: death by suicide, diagnosis of major depressive disorder (DSM-IV), 22 absence of psychotropic or illegal drugs on toxicological screens, death without prolonged agonal state or protracted medical illness.",
